My name is Philip R. Cyr. I was a platoon corpsman and latter the Senior corpsman, (HM2) of G 2/7, 1st Mar Div, Vietnam 1967-68.  I was WIA on Charlie Ridge March 26, 1968 and medivaced to USNH, Yokuska, Japan. After three weeks there I was again medivaced to USNH Portsmouth, VA, ward 4 A. and again to USNH Portsmouth, N. H. I was discharged there on June 13, 1969.<br>
Prior to Vietnam I was with F 2/8, 2nd Mar Div. I was deployed on a BLT in the Carib. Nov. 66-May 67. August, 1966 to September 1967.<br>
Prior to being a &quot;grunt&quot; I was a ward jocky at USNH Newport R. I. January 1966 to August 1966.<br>
I was in Company 13 at Hospital Corps School, Great Lakes, Ill, fall of 65 to graduation right after Christmas. <br><br>
Is there anyone out there that served with me??
